<h1>Community</h1>

<p>This is you!</p>

<h2>Mailing Lists</h2>

<p>We're currently hosting the <strong>bolo</strong> mailing list at <a href="mailto:bolo@groups.io">bolo@groups.io</a>.
You can view the web archives <a href="https://groups.io/g/bolo">here</a>, and subscribe via
<a href="mailto:bolo+subscribe@groups.io">bolo+subscribe@groups.io</a>.</p>

<h2>IRC</h2>

<p>We're in <code>#bolo</code> on <a href="http://www.oftc.net">OFTC</a>, stop by and chat with us some time.</p>

<h2>Community Roadmap</h2>

<p>We're missing a lot of stuff, and we know it.  Here's the current plan:</p>

<ul>
<li>Set up mailling lists</li>
<li>Write the <a href="/start">Getting Started</a> guide</li>
<li>Write up some architectural <a href="/docs">documentation</a></li>
<li>Set up Package Builds (probably via Travis)</li>
<li>Host APT/YUM repositories</li>
</ul>

<h2>Hacking on Bolo</h2>

<p>To get started, you'll need the bolo core and the collectors:</p>

<pre><code>$ cd ~/code
$ git clone https://github.com/bolo/bolo.git
...
$ git clone https://github.com/bolo/bolo-collectors.git
...
</code></pre>

<p>To build bolo, you'll need a recent vintage of 0MQ, <a href="https://github.com/filefrog/libvigor">libvigor</a> and
<a href="https://github.com/filefrog/ctap">ctap</a> for the tests.</p>

<p>bolo-collectors only needs <a href="https://github.com/filefrog/libvigor">libvigor</a>.</p>

<h2>Continuous Integration</h2>

<p>We use Travis.</p>

<ul>
<li>bolo: <a href="https://travis-ci.org/bolo/bolo"><img src="https://travis-ci.org/bolo/bolo.svg?branch=master" alt="Build Status" title=""></a></li>
<li>bolo-collectors: <a href="https://travis-ci.org/bolo/bolo-collectors"><img src="https://travis-ci.org/bolo/bolo-collectors.svg?branch=master" alt="Build Status" title=""></a></li>
</ul>
